org.spongepowered.api.util.ban

Interface Ban

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Ban.Ip, Ban.Profile

    public interface Ban
    Represents a ban made on an object.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  Ban.Builder
      Represents a builder that creates bans.
      static interface  Ban.Ip
      Represents a ban made on an IP.
      static interface  Ban.Profile
      Represents a ban made on a GameProfile.

      • getCreationDate

        Instant getCreationDate()
        Gets the creation date of the ban.

        Note that this Instant has no effect on whether or not a ban is active. Any ban for which BanService.hasBan(Ban) returns true will be used (when checking if a player can join, for example), regardless of its creation date.

        Returns:
        Creation date of the ban

      • getBanSource

        Optional<Text> getBanSource()
        Gets the source that created this ban, if available.

        Depending on the implementation, the returned Text may represent a CommandSource. getBanCommandSource() can be used to attempt to convert the source to a CommandSource.

        Returns:
        the source of this ban, if available

      • getBanCommandSource

        Optional<CommandSource> getBanCommandSource()
        Gets the source that created this ban in CommandSource form, if available.

        Depending on the implementation, it may not be possible to determine the CommandSource responsible for this ban. Because of this, it is recommended to check getBanSource() if this method returns Optional.empty().

        Returns:
        The banning source or Optional.empty()

      • getExpirationDate

        Optional<Instant> getExpirationDate()
        Gets the expiration date of this ban, if available.
        Returns:
        Expiration time of the ban or Optional.empty()

      • isIndefinite

        default boolean isIndefinite()
        Gets whether this ban is indefinitely long, e.g. has no expiration date.
        Returns:
        True if this ban has no expiration date, otherwise false
